news.title: Ludhiana civic body asks development body to pay Rs 47 crore for 'illegal' sewer connections
news.para: On Friday, a meeting took place at MC's zone-D office where MC commissioner Shena Aggarwal asked the Glada officials to first pay the EDC charges.

news.title: Lenders seek buyers for bankrupt Golden Jubilee Hotel's Rs 652 crore debt
news.para: The Hyderabad NCLT had approved a Rs 584 crore offer from Blackstone in February 2020, but the plan was not implemented due to land-related disputes.  Lenders have set a reserve price of Rs 400 crore, implying a recovery of 61% on principal dues.

news.title: Cochin development body to submit concept plan of economic city to government
news.para: The GCDA will submit a detailed concept plan of the project to the state government next week and the process of preparing a detailed project report (DPR) would begin after the government gives approval for the plan.

news.title: Lokayukta conducts raids over illegal sand extraction in Mangaluru
news.para: The officials have seized trucks, an earthmover machine, sand and other items worth Rs 40 lakh. The seized properties were handed over to the jurisdictional police stations, and three criminal cases have been registered.

news.title: MIDC looking for land for proposed IT Park near Nashik
news.para: The official, while talking to TOI, said the proposed IT Park will be around 10-km away from Nashik city and the process of identifying the land is underway.

news.title: Process soon to convert land to free-hold in Bhubaneswar & Cuttack
news.para: It was decided at a high-level meeting chaired by chief secretary Suresh Chandra Mahapatra here on Friday. He advised the officials to decentralise the decision-making process for converting lease-hold land to free-hold land.

news.title: Berhampur civic body to demolish 90 slum houses
news.para: The affected families were already allotted houses constructed about a year ago under the Rajiv Awas Yojana (RAY) at Jagabandhu Sahi (64) and Auto Nagar (26).

news.title: NCLT approves amalgamation of MITL & MRDL with Mahindra World City Developers
news.para: Mahindra World City Developers will issue, to the shareholders of MITL, 325 fully paid-up redeemable preference shares of MWCDL of Rs 10 each for every 100 equity shares of Rs 10 each held in MITL, it said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Amid layoffs, flexible workspace players on expansion overdrive in Hyderabad
news.para: Hyderabad's flex market has zoomed to about 6 million sq ft with about 85,000 seats since 2018 with most of it concentrated in HiTec City area.

news.title: Telangana CM lays foundation stone for Rs 6,250 crore Hyderabad Airport Metro
news.para: The project, starting at Mindspace junction to Shamshabad (Hyderabad International Airport) Airport, would cost approximately Rs 6,250 crore, Rao said.

news.title: Farmhouses in Aravalis to be razed from December 12
news.para: A total of 424 farmhouses in Sohna were deemed to have been constructed illegally on land that is protected under Section 4 of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA) as ‘gair mumkin pahar (uncultivable hill)’.

news.title: Deadline over, not even 20% of Supertech twin towers' rubble lifted in Noida
news.para: Officials attribute the delay in clearing all the debris to various reasons, including the implementation of the graded response action plan (GRAP) to contain pollution to non-payment of fees for processing the rubble by the developer, Supertech.

news.title: Sunac China proposes deleveraging plan to restructure debt
news.para: Sunac is one of the biggest property developers in China that has been reeling under debt woes. The company last month proposed a plan to restructure and extend its onshore debts.

news.title: Elan Group raises $60 million from PAG for construction of realty projects, growth
news.para: The investment will be used towards growth capital to endorse existing debt and to scale up construction of its new luxury housing project -- "The Presidential", located in Sector 106 Gurugram.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body plans new funding for two metro corridors
news.para: The logic the GDA has put forth is that no state development authority is bearing the whole cost of a metro project and the same formula should be applied to these two Ghaziabad metro extension projects as well.
